  "prompt": "What is the use of microbeads in cosmetics?",
  "response": "Microbeads are tiny plastic particles that have been used in cosmetics and personal care products for several purposes:\n\n1. **Exfoliation**: Microbeads are commonly found in products like facial scrubs and body washes. They help in gently removing dead skin cells from the surface of the skin, promoting a smoother and more radiant complexion.\n\n2. **Texture**: In some cosmetics, microbeads are included to improve the texture and feel of the product. They can give products a silky, smooth consistency that feels pleasant on the skin.\n\n3. **Color and Aesthetics**: Microbeads can add visual appeal to products. They may be used to give a product a glittery or pearlescent look that can make it more attractive to consumers.\n\nDespite their utility in cosmetics, microbeads have raised environmental concerns due to their non-biodegradable nature. When washed down the drain, they can pass through water treatment systems and end up in rivers and oceans, contributing to plastic pollution and harming marine life.\n\nDue to these environmental impacts, many countries have banned or restricted the use of microbeads in cosmetic products. Companies are increasingly turning to natural or biodegradable alternatives, such as ground seeds, salt, sugar, and other natural exfoliants, to replace microbeads in their formulations.",
